---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Terms of Service — NomsAI"
  description="NomsAI terms of service. Simple, fair terms for using the AI calorie tracker. Last updated 6 March 2026."
>

  <article class="py-16 sm:py-24 bg-[#f4f2ef] dark:bg-[#0a0a0a]">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">

      <!-- Header -->
      <header class="mb-12">
        <p class="text-sm font-bold uppercase tracking-widest mb-3" style="color:#c8920a">Legal</p>
        <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-[#1c1714] dark:text-white mb-3">Terms of Service</h1>
        <p style="color:#6b6560">Last updated: 6 March 2026 · NomsAI by a solo developer</p>

        <div class="mt-8 rounded-2xl p-6 border-l-4" style="background:#edeae5;border-color:#c8920a">
          <p class="font-semibold text-[#1c1714] dark:text-white mb-1">Plain English:</p>
          <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed" style="color:#6b6560">
            NomsAI is a calorie-tracking tool, not a medical device. Use it sensibly, don't abuse the service, and understand that AI macro estimates are approximations. By using the app you agree to these terms.
          </p>
        </div>
      </header>

      <div class="prose-legal">

        <h2>1. Acceptance</h2>
        <p>By downloading, installing, or using NomsAI ("the App"), you agree to be bound by these Terms. If you do not agree, do not use the App. For questions, contact <a href="mailto:hello@nomsai.app">hello@nomsai.app</a>.</p>

        <h2>2. Description of Service</h2>
        <p>NomsAI is a macro-tracking application that uses AI (Google Gemini) to estimate the nutritional content of meals from free-text descriptions. The App also allows you to log workouts, track weight, and set dietary goals. It is an <strong>informational tool only</strong>.</p>

        <h2>3. Eligibility</h2>
        <p>You must be at least 13 years old (16 in the EEA) to use the App. By using the App you confirm that you meet this requirement.</p>

        <h2>4. No Medical Advice</h2>
        <p>NomsAI is <strong>not a medical device</strong> and does not provide medical, clinical, nutritional, or dietary advice. Macro and calorie estimates are AI-generated approximations — they may be inaccurate. <strong>Do not use this App to manage any medical condition, eating disorder, or health emergency.</strong> Always consult a qualified healthcare professional before making changes to your diet or exercise regime.</p>

        <h2>5. Accuracy of AI Estimates</h2>
        <p>Calorie and macro figures produced by the App are estimates. Actual nutritional content varies by brand, preparation method, portion size, and ingredient variation. We make no warranty that any estimate is accurate, complete, or fit for any particular purpose.</p>

        <h2>6. Credits and Purchases</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Free credits</strong> — New users receive welcome credits and a daily allocation of free AI logs. These are provided at our discretion and may be adjusted at any time.</li>
          <li><strong>Purchased credits and Supporter Pass</strong> — Payments are processed by Apple App Store or Google Play. All sales are final. Refunds are handled per Apple's and Google's refund policies.</li>
          <li><strong>Supporter Pass (annual/monthly)</strong> — Provides unlimited AI logs subject to a daily fair-use limit. Subscriptions auto-renew unless cancelled before the renewal date.</li>
          <li><strong>No cash value</strong> — Credits have no monetary value, are non-transferable, and expire if your account is deleted.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>7. Acceptable Use</h2>
        <p>You agree not to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Attempt to circumvent credit limits, reverse-engineer the App, or abuse the AI API.</li>
          <li>Use automated tools, scripts, or bots to interact with the App or its API.</li>
          <li>Submit illegal, harmful, or abusive content as food-entry text.</li>
          <li>Resell, sublicense, or commercially exploit any part of the App or its API.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>8. Intellectual Property</h2>
        <p>All content, design, code, and branding in the App are owned by or licensed to us. You are granted a personal, non-exclusive, non-transferable licence to use the App for your own personal, non-commercial purposes.</p>

        <h2>9. Your Data</h2>
        <p>Our collection and use of your data is described in our <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>, which forms part of these Terms. Your food logs, workout logs, and weight data are stored only on your device and are never transmitted to our servers.</p>

        <h2>10. Third-Party Services</h2>
        <p>The App relies on Google Gemini (AI), RevenueCat (payments), Apple App Store, and Google Play. Your use of those services is governed by their respective terms. We are not responsible for third-party service availability or accuracy.</p>

        <h2>11. Disclaimers</h2>
        <p>The App is provided <strong>"as is"</strong> without warranties of any kind. To the fullest extent permitted by law, we disclaim all implied warranties including merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose, and non-infringement.</p>

        <h2>12. Limitation of Liability</h2>
        <p>To the fullest extent permitted by applicable law, we shall not be liable for any indirect, incidental, special, consequential, or punitive damages arising from your use of the App, including loss of data, personal injury, or health consequences resulting from reliance on AI-generated nutritional estimates.</p>
        <p>Our total aggregate liability to you shall not exceed the amount you paid us in the twelve months preceding the claim.</p>

        <h2>13. Governing Law</h2>
        <p>These Terms are governed by the laws of England and Wales. Any disputes shall be subject to the exclusive jurisdiction of the courts of England and Wales.</p>

        <h2>14. Changes</h2>
        <p>We may modify or discontinue the App at any time. We may update these Terms; continued use after changes constitutes acceptance.</p>

        <h2>15. Contact</h2>
        <p><a href="mailto:hello@nomsai.app">hello@nomsai.app</a></p>

      </div>
    </div>
  </article>

</Layout>

<style>
  .prose-legal h2 {
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #1c1714;
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    padding-top: 1.5rem;
    border-top: 1px solid #d4ccc4;
  }
  :global(.dark) .prose-legal h2 {
    color: white;
    border-top-color: #2a2a2a;
  }
  .prose-legal p {
    color: #6b6560;
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }
  :global(.dark) .prose-legal p { color: #9ca3af; }
  .prose-legal ul {
    list-style: disc;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }
  .prose-legal li {
    color: #6b6560;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }
  :global(.dark) .prose-legal li { color: #9ca3af; }
  .prose-legal a { color: #c8920a; text-decoration: underline; }
  .prose-legal strong { color: #1c1714; }
  :global(.dark) .prose-legal strong { color: white; }
</style>
